In a press briefing, President Trump announced that he will be traveling to Kansas City to make a speech on law enforcement. He confirmed that Bill Barr, a highly respected lawyer and former Attorney General under the Bush administration, will be nominated for the United States Attorney General position. Trump also announced that Heather Nauert, who has worked with Mike Pompeo at the State Department, will be nominated as the Ambassador to the United Nations, replacing Nikki Haley. The President hinted at another announcement regarding the Joint Chiefs of Staff and succession to be made at the Army-Navy game.